So apparently the air quality in NYC is worst than any other city on earth due to a huge fire that occurred in Canada and New Jersey. The air quality right now is at the point where it is hazardous to the people. Here are a few tips and precautions to consider during these times… (feel free to add any that you might think is beneficial)

1. Ditch the masks (unless it’s a high quality one that filters the air as you breathe)

2. Get a air purifier 

3. Get some snake plants

4. Get some herbs that aid the respiratory system such as…
• Mullein Leaf
• Nettle 
• Plantain Leaf
• Licorice Root
• Sea Moss

5. Learn how to breathe properly, in through the nose and out through the mouth. Make sure your stomach goes up when you inhale and goes down when exhale. 

(Bonus) 6. Get next to water if you can. The ocean is responsible for most of our oxygen (up to 85%)
